  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Sales Engineer</strong></p><p>The role is to market a full range of Professional & Industrial Cleaning equipment, and accessories & tools, to corporate customers, with an emphasis in petrochemical, oil refinery, shipyard, oil & gas sectors. <br /><br />Product range includes high-pressure water jetting pumps, vacuum pumps, valves, hoses, motors, engines, robotic pumps etc<br /><br />The successful applicant has to</p><p>- serve existing assigned accounts while actively prospecting and acquiring new customers</p><p>- learn & familiarise our products well, understand users’ needs, and so be able to offer solutions and assistance to meet their requirements</p><p>- perform hands-on product demonstrations, as well as occasionally conduct presentations to mid-size audiences including management levels<br /></p><p>Candidate should</p><ul><li>be customer and sales oriented</li><li>possess a strong sense of self-discipline, integrity & initiative; work well independently, yet be a good team player</li><li>own basic IT skills in document, presentation & spreadsheet softwares; WhatsApp and other common apps</li><li>have earned a Polytechnic Diploma or equivalent; preferably in a business associated or engineering related field …..</li><li>…and/or be experienced in corporate/industrial sales, especially in the oil and gas setting</li><li>preferably hold a Class 3 driving license and own a car</li></ul><p>We offer an attractive compensation package comprising basic salary, transport allowance / transport reimbursement, and sales target incentive.</p>",
